  "source_id": "migraine",
  "name": "Migraine - Triptan Medication Query (High-Specificity)",
  "description": "Tests ability to find migraine patients via triptan medications — sumatriptan, rizatriptan, eletriptan, zolmitriptan, naratriptan. **Triptans are highly migraine-specific** (essentially no other indication), so Path C cross-indication is minimal. This contrasts with biologics, anticoagulants, and steroids — making triptans a clean signal for migraine cohort identification.",
  "prompt": "Find patients prescribed triptan medications used for migraine, including sumatriptan, rizatriptan, eletriptan, zolmitriptan, or naratriptan.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on triptans.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed triptan-class medications used for acute migraine attacks — sumatriptan, rizatriptan, eletriptan, zolmitriptan, and naratriptan. Triptans are 5-HT1B/1D receptor agonists used almost exclusively for migraine.",
    "expert": "I need MedicationRequest resources for any triptan. Use these RxNorm ingredient codes: 37418 (sumatriptan), 88014 (rizatriptan), 231049 (eletriptan), 135775 (zolmitriptan), 141366 (naratriptan). Combine in a single comma-separated code search. Triptans have minimal cross-indication — they are essentially migraine-specific drugs, making this a high-precision medication-based query."
  },
